Instead of writing the
surface as a capital sigma,

00:00:06.660 --> 00:00:09.610
I've written it as a capital S.
Instead of writing d lowercase

00:00:09.610 --> 00:00:11.770
sigma, I wrote d uppercase
S, which is still

00:00:11.770 --> 00:00:13.797
a surface integral
of the function y.

00:00:13.797 --> 00:00:16.130
And the surface we care about
is x plus y squared mins z

00:00:16.130 --> 00:00:16.713
is equal to 0.

00:00:18.890 --> 00:00:22.390
X between 0 and 1,
y between 0 and 2.

